answers.body_markdown:
Your struct `llist` has no constructor, and so the following line in `main` will default-initialize it:

    llist *head = new llist;

Now, none of the members of the object pointed to by `head` are initialized and your program has undefined behavior because you attempt to use them (in `addItem`) before initializing.

You can fix this by either specifying an appropriate default constructor (that zero-initializes each member), or by zero-initializing the object when you create it:

* Default constructor example:

        struct llist {
            llist()
                : size(0)
                , first(nullptr)
                , last(nullptr)
            { }

            int size;
            litemLL *first;
            litemLL *last;
        };

* Zero-initialize example:

        llist *head = new llist();

